● You already have a preview profile configured for APK builds. You just need EAS
   CLI and an Expo account. Run these steps in order:

  1. Install EAS CLI
  npm install -g eas-cli

  2. Log in to Expo (create a free account at expo.dev if you don't have one)    
  eas login

  3. Link your project to Expo (one-time setup)
  eas build:configure

  4. Build the APK (runs in the cloud, takes ~5-10 min)
  eas build --platform android --profile preview

  When the build finishes, EAS gives you a download link for the .apk file.      
  Transfer it to your Android device and install it (you'll need to allow        
  "Install from unknown sources" in your Android settings).

  ---
  Note: The preview profile in your eas.json already has "buildType": "apk" and  
  "distribution": "internal" set correctly — you don't need to change anything.  

  If you want to build completely offline/locally without EAS (requires Android  
  Studio + SDK installed), the alternative is:
  npx expo run:android --variant release
  But EAS cloud build is much easier and doesn't require Android Studio.

